The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Oct. 5: The income tax department has raised a demand of about Rs 570 crore on Mahindra Satyam for illegally claiming tax credit on fictitious income between 2003-04 and 2008-09. We have asked the company to pay about Rs 570 crore as tax, as the company claimed the credit on tax which it did not pay overseas, official sources said.                             
	 New Delhi, Oct. 5: The World Bank has barred three Indian companies  Ambalal Sarabhai Enterprises, Mumbai-based Chemito Technologies, New Delhi-based Global Spin Weave  from participating in World Bank projects for indulging in fraudulent practices while doing business with it.                            
	 Mumbai, Oct. 5: RBI deputy governor Subir Gokarn has hinted at responding to the surge in capital inflows if it leads to any disruptions. When we see signs of disruptions caused by capital inflows and impact on domestic market exchange rate, thats the basis to respond, he said.
                                                                                                                          
